LISTERIOSIS, MEAT RECALLS - USA: EXPANDED
****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
<http://www.fas.org/ahead>
See Also
Listeriosis, meat recall - USA (Missouri) 990117112746
Listeriosis, meat recall - USA (Wisconsin) 990116210032
Listeriosis, meat recalls - USA (Arkansas & Ohio) 990124005341
Date: Mon, 01 Feb 1999 18:51:14 -0500
From: "Robert A. LaBudde" <ral@lcfltd.com>
Source: FSNET

CHICAGO -- Consumer products maker Sara Lee Corp. was cited as saying
today that it had added more brands to the list of packaged meat
products it recalled in December because of possible contamination by
Listeria.
The story says that while the foodservice operators stopped using the
Sara Lee products at the restaurants, hospitals and other venues they
serve, they may have sold them at outlet stores before the recall date.
Sara Lee spokeswoman Theresa Herlevsen was cited as saying the
additional recalled brands total about 200 000 pounds of meat, and that
it expects to recover a total of about 15 million pounds of meat in the
massive recall.
The additional brands being recalled were sold by Grand Rapids,
Mich.-based Gordon Food Service, which operates about 70 stores; Allen
Foods, which has one outlet store in St. Louis; Sara Lee's PYA Monarch
foodservice unit, which runs two stores in Montgomery, Ala.; and a Bil
Mar Country Store outlet in Zeeland, Mich.
